# AirSpice reference-engine environment.
#
# Copy to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values as needed.
# EVERY value here is OPTIONAL: with none of them set, the app still starts and
# all non-simulation features work. See docs/DEVELOPMENT.md for the full table of
# what degrades when each is missing.
#
# NEVER commit a real API key or a machine-specific tool path. This file holds
# placeholders only.

# --- LLM provider key (optional) --------------------------------------------
# Used by the AI generate/repair commands when --provider gemini is selected.
# Without it, those commands fail with a clear "no API key" message; the mock
# provider (the default) and every non-AI feature keep working.
# Get one at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here

# --- External tool overrides (optional) -------------------------------------
# The engine resolves each tool by checking its AIR_* override first, then PATH
# (see air/tools.py). Set an override only when the binary lives outside PATH
# (portable build, per-user install, vendored toolchain). Leave unset to use
# PATH. When a tool is missing entirely, the feature that needs it degrades
# gracefully with an actionable diagnostic instead of crashing.

# Real analog transient simulation. Missing -> `simulate`/`check` fall back to
# the built-in DC solver and emit an NGSPICE_NOT_FOUND diagnostic.
# Install: https://ngspice.sourceforge.io/download.html
# AIR_NGSPICE=/absolute/path/to/ngspice

# ISA-level firmware co-simulation. Missing -> Renode-backed commands are
# unavailable; analog-only and DC features are unaffected.
# Install: https://renode.io/#downloads
# AIR_RENODE=/absolute/path/to/renode

# Firmware builds (PlatformIO). Missing -> build-firmware is unavailable; design,
# validation, compile, and analog simulation are unaffected.
# `pip install platformio` (its console script is typically named `platformio` or `pio`).
# AIR_PLATFORMIO=/absolute/path/to/platformio
# AIR_PIO=/absolute/path/to/pio
